  "section_name": "Risk Analysis",
  "text": "Operational execution risk is suggested by earnings volatility throughout 2025. Net income growth fluctuated significantly across quarters, declining 18.37% in Q2 before rebounding 24.06% in Q3, then contracting 1.50% in Q4. This variability indicates potential sensitivity to market conditions or operational factors that could affect profitability consistency. Additionally, R&D intensity reached 16.31% of revenue in Q4 2025, with $18,572,000,000 in R&D expenses. While this investment level supports innovation capabilities, it represents substantial ongoing commitment that must generate adequate returns to justify the expenditure.",
